node.text: @msrachelhollis👇 (link in bio) We talk about loving yourself and seeing failure as success. We all need to learn to see the positive aspects of every failure in our life, to take proper care of ourselves by taking good care of our health, to sit down and process pain and grief at our own pace, and to never lose ourselves just to keep a relationship.

node.text: @jadapinkettsmith Happy Birthday to my soul friend 🎁🎉😇 I’m so deeply grateful you were born. You’re such a powerful force for good in the world through everything you do! You do everything with so much passion, grace and strength and it’s a joy to watch you serve in your purpose. You have one of the most generous and kind hearts and have brought so much depth into our lives. I can’t wait to see the impact you continue to have on humanity and the next stage of your service. It is an honor to call you a dear spiritual friend and I have absolutely loved all the discussions and conversations we’ve had and the community we’ve created. Go wish Jada a Happy Birthday everyone 🎂🎈🥳

node.text: There is so much opportunity for presence when you are sitting down and having a cup of tea. For me, tea has become a constant symbol for presence, attention, and energy in my life, even when life gets hectic. You may not have all the time in the world, but tea is one way of finding presence and sharing a purposeful moment with someone you love. Go to samatea.com/ig (link in bio) to get a free 5-minute journal made to help you find moments of presence.

May be a closeup of 1 person, beard, standing and text that says 'WSJ MAGAZINE believe we become better people, better partners, better professionals, better parents when we know our purpose and we live our purpose," says Jay Shetty the 34-year-old author, podcast host and former monk.'.

node.text:
Honored & grateful for this profile in @wsjmag about my journey so far. It’s so important to look back and reflect for each of us and it is as important to look forward and consistently redefine ourselves for the future. There have been many rejections, many failures and mistakes along the way but at the same time there has been love, joy and so many fulfilling opportunities. The thing I’m most grateful for is the fact that I get to connect with so many of you, from different backgrounds and walks of life. I love seeing school teachers show my videos in their classrooms, or frontline workers reading my book, or the millions of you that listen to the podcast every week through to people in the worlds of business, music and entertainment. All of you matter and all of you have a purpose. If I can help you find, ignite and live your purpose so that you can serve the world then my life will be a success. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
I want to express my deepest, sincerest appreciation to anyone that has helped and supported me, consciously or unconsciously along the way. This is just the beginning!

Stylist @hemaapersad 
Hair @themensgroomer 
Outfit @yony_la
